text: [Music]
the Green Knight once upon a time in the
great kingdom of Caplin lived king
duster king duster had only one daughter
called Rachel and she was the most
dearest to him than anything in the
world everyone who saw her thought that
she would grow up to be as beautiful and
charming as her mother who had passed
away when she was born Princess Rachel
often missed her mother and the king was
aware of it he felt sorry for her it so
happened one day that near the king's
palace came to live a noble lady called
lady Trish and her little girl Vantaa
Vantaa was about the same age as
Princess Rachel Princess Rachel and
Vantaa soon became friends and lady
Trish would be in the palace most of the
time looking after the two girls while
they played lady Trish was very kind to
the princess and treated her with love
princess Rachel and Vantaa played
together and grew up together everything
was fine in the princess's life until
one day as she was walking in the
kingdom gardens lady Trish came to her
dressed for a journey where are you off
to
farewell my child I must leave you and
go far away what yes and when will you
be back
I'm afraid never no please don't go what
will I do without you it breaks my heart
to go dear child but I must go is there
nothing that can keep you here only one

impossible tell me what it is and I will
make sure it is done I would stay if
your father would make me his queen

leave it to me and it will be done
Princess Rachel went to her father

deprived of mother's love once again
please marry her father I am very fond

him to I do not want to marry her my
child but if this is what is going to

Rachel was ecstatic thank you so much

soon after the wedding was celebrated

time lady Trish's manner towards the
princess began to change she was jealous

daughter was heir to the throne
soon her true colors came out instead of
speaking kindly and lovingly to the
princess her words became rough and
cruel that is a nice dress you are
wedding I want you to give it to vantaa
at once but mother I love this dress
I don't care I am The Queen do not
forget that now get out of my sight the
Queen's behavior towards the princess
became worse with every passing day
and the princess could take it no more
she was sad and upset all day crying in
her room
the King was very unhappy at seeing his
loved daughter suffer and could no
longer bear it he decided to build her a
castle on the island in the lake here it
is your very own castle live here
happily away from your stepmother here
you can do whatever you want and I will
make sure that your stepmother never
enters it thank you so much father
promise me you will come visit me every
day that goes without saying my love the
princess hugged her father for a long
time she lived in peace and grew more
and more beautiful every day one day a
messenger from the neighboring kingdom
came to invite King duster to a great
meeting of knights and Nobles king
duster accepted the invitation before
setting out he went to take leave of his
daughter my love I am going to the great
meetings of knights and Nobles
there will be splendid shops set up
especially for princesses like you is
there anything I can get for you from
there I do not want anything father but
if you would greet the Green Knight from
me I'd be thankful sure my love I will
do that king duster had never heard of
the Green Knight but there was no time
to ask questions
therefore he gave the promise and rode
off on his journey while on his journey
he asked everyone he saw about the Green
Knight do you know the Green Knight but
the answer was always no king duster
began to believe that his daughter was
mistaken about the existence of the
Green Knight he was sad that it was the
first time she had asked him to do
something for her and he could not do it
he thought so much about it that he did
not notice the direction his horse was
taking and presently he found himself in
the midst of a dense forest
where he had never been before he rode
on and on looking for the path at last
to his delight he saw a man he rode up
to him I'd lost my way can you tell me
where I am you're in the Green Knights
forest king duster was ecstatic where
does the Green Knight live oh not far
from here the man explained to him the
directions king duster thanked him and
rode on finally he reached a beautiful
castle standing in the midst of a lovely
garden where fountains played in marble
bases on the edge of a marble basin sat
a young and handsome men who was dressed
from head to foot in a suit of green
armor king duster went up to him you
must be the Green Knight yes they call
me that because I am always dressed in
green but my real name is Eugene I'm so
glad to have finally found you I was on
my way to the great meeting of knights
and Nobles but lost my way while trying
to find your palace what is it that you
come to ask of me sir well I have come
to give you my daughter's greeting I've
never met you or your daughter before
but you are very welcome to stay in my
palace for the night the Sun is setting
down and for you to go back through the
forest now is not advisable king duster
was thankful and accepted the invitation
next morning when king duster was about
to set forth on his journey home Prince
Eugene put into his hand a jeweled
casket your highness please carry this
gift to your daughter it contains my
portrait and when I came to see her she
will know me I am very certain that she
is the lady I have seen night after
night in my dreams and I must win her
for my bride the king gave the knight
his blessing and promised to take the
gift to his daughter
with that he set off when he reached her
palace princess Rachel ran towards him
did you see the Green Knight yes I did
and his real name is Prince Eugene
Prince Eugene Wow
he has asked me to give you this gift so
that you will know who he is when he
arrives when the princess saw the
portrait she was delighted
it is indeed the man who I have seen in
my dreams father I will marry no one but
him all right if that is what you wish
my love but I would suggest you meet him
first meanwhile make sure your
stepmother doesn't find out about it
very soon after Prince Eugene arrived
and he looked so handsome in his green
armor the princess fell in love with him
even more when he saw her and recognized
her as the lady whom he had so often
dreamt of he immediately asked her to be
his bride will you marry me the princess
looked down and smiled yes they hugged
each other just then Princess Rachel
remembered her father's advice but
listen we must keep the secret from my
stepmother until the wedding day
otherwise she will find a way to ruin it
all as you wish but I cannot stay away
from you any longer
until the wedding day I will meet you
every day I will come early in the
morning and leave when it is dark that
way your stepmother will never find out
about us for the next few days Prince
Eugene visited the princess every day
and spent many hours wandering with her
through the beautiful gardens where they
knew the Queen could not see them
one day a girl who was walking by the
lake early in the morning saw the prince
rode to the princess's castle where
Princess Rachel awaited him she soon
went to the Queen and told her
everything
the Queen was furious the next day early
in the morning the Queen went down to
the shore of the lake with a bottle of
magic potion and hid herself behind the
tree Prince Eugene came as usual spent
the day with Princess Rachel and when it
was almost dusk he went to the bank and
sat on the boat unaware that the Queen
had applied the magic potion all over
the handle of the oar he held it and
started rowing it is so hot with the
magic potion all over his palms Prince
Eugene wiped his forehead
the potion soon mixed with his skin and
slowly started turning him green when
Prince Eugene reached his palace he felt
very ill for the next few days
Princess Rachel longed for Prince Eugene
but he did not come as he was sick but
she did not know of this she felt
helpless as her father was also out of
the Kingdom to visit the other Kings for
matters of trade
she sat by the open window crying and
feeling very sad just then a little bird
came and sat on the branch of the tree
that stood just underneath your princess
said you must go to him immediately
what's what happened to Annie there is
no time for explanation just know that
your evil stepmother has used a magic
potion on him and only the yellow herbs
in your garden can save him tell me more
please dress yourself as a nurse from
the palace of the country King for it is
the only way you will be allowed near
the prince make soup out of the yellow
hurts and give it to him when he
finishes the bowl he will recover
instantly the next day a princess Rachel
left early in the morning dressed as a
nurse carrying with her the yellow
Holmes
the bird flew ahead of her to give her
directions to the palace and when they
reached the palace princess Rachel at
once went to the princes most trusted
old nurse madam my name is Fiona and I
have been sent by the country's King to
help in the princes recovery and how do
you intend to do that when even our best
doctors have failed the potion is fatal
and it breaks my heart to say that no
one can help the prince oh but I can you
see with my herbal soup the prince will
recover at once and why should I trust
you do you have any other choice the old
nurse thought that it was worth giving a
try she agreed all right you can go to
the princes room with the soup Princess
Rachel said the ailing Prince with her
own hens after finishing the entire bowl
of the soup she went outside and waited
for some time soon Prince Eugene started
sweating and within moments he recovered
completely when he woke up Princess
Rachel sent inside a young nurse with
the empty bowl of soup in her hand
who are you is it you who made this soup
that has cured me yes well choose
whatever you wish is a reward and you
shall have it
the young nurse had already been taught
by Princess Rachel what to say I want to
be your bride I am sorry
but that is the one thing I cannot grant
from my heart belongs to the most
beautiful girl in the world and she
waits for me in her island palace
hearing this princess Rachel ran inside
the princes room and hugged him tight
the young nurse smiled and left
the prince was delighted to see her but
also confused what is going on Princess
Rachel explained to him everything and
how it was her stepmother who would used
a magic potion to make him fall sick I
am so glad you saved me my love I am
glad you are fine the two held hands and
hugged each other once again soon they
were married with great splendour king
duster was delighted to see his daughter
so happy and as for the Queen and her
daughter he sent them out of the kingdom
and warned them to never set foot in his
territory Prince Eugene and Princess
Rachel lived in their Island palace and
also helped king duster in running his
kingdom under them the people of the
kingdom were very very happy
